and, as usual, it's spot on.

255
00:17:23,539 --> 00:17:25,495
Can you get nothing wrong?

256
00:17:25,539 --> 00:17:27,689
You flatter me, Captain.

257
00:17:29,459 --> 00:17:32,371
Dr Doppler, I presume?

258
00:17:32,419 --> 00:17:34,216
Yes. I...

259
00:17:34,259 --> 00:17:37,331
- Hello! Can you hear me?
- Yes! Stop that banging!

260
00:17:37,379 --> 00:17:39,973
If I may, Doctor,
this works so much better...

261
00:17:40,019 --> 00:17:42,613
when it's right-way up
and plugged in.

262
00:17:42,659 --> 00:17:44,058
Lovely. There you go.

263
00:17:44,099 --> 00:17:46,659
If you don't mind,
I can manage my own plugging!

264
00:17:46,699 --> 00:17:47,739
I'm Captain Amelia...

265
00:17:47,739 --> 00:17:47,977
I'm Captain Amelia...

266
00:17:48,019 --> 00:17:49,532
late of a few run-ins
with the Protean armada.

267
00:17:49,579 --> 00:17:51,570
Nasty business, but I won't
bore you with my scars.

268
00:17:51,619 --> 00:17:53,371
You've met
my first officer, Mr Arrow.

269
00:17:53,419 --> 00:17:55,330
Sterling, tough, dependable,
honest, brave, and true.

270
00:17:55,379 --> 00:17:57,051
Please, Captain.

271
00:17:57,099 --> 00:17:58,976
Shut up, Arrow.
I don't mean a word of it.

272
00:17:59,019 --> 00:18:02,136
Excuse me. I hate to interrupt
this lovely banter...

273
00:18:02,179 --> 00:18:04,613
but may I introduce to you,
Jim Hawkins?

274
00:18:04,659 --> 00:18:07,776
Jim, you see, is the boy
who found the treasure...

275
00:18:07,819 --> 00:18:09,775
Doctor, please!

276
00:18:12,419 --> 00:18:14,728
I'd like a word with you
in my stateroom.

277
00:18:16,179 --> 00:18:21,207
Doctor, to muse and blabber
about a treasure map...

278
00:18:21,259 --> 00:18:23,136
in front of
this particular crew...

279
00:18:23,179 --> 00:18:25,295
demonstrates
a level of ineptitude...

280
00:18:25,339 --> 00:18:27,455
that borders
on the imbecilic...

281
00:18:27,499 --> 00:18:29,410
and I mean that
in a very caring way.

282
00:18:29,459 --> 00:18:32,690
Imbecilic, did you say?
Foolishness, I've...

283
00:18:32,739 --> 00:18:34,377
May I see the map, please?

284
00:18:39,779 --> 00:18:41,007
Here.

285
00:18:42,379 --> 00:18:44,768
Fascinating.

286
00:18:46,379 --> 00:18:48,256
Mr Hawkins, in the future...

287
00:18:48,299 --> 00:18:50,051
you will address me
as "Captain" or "Ma'am."

288
00:18:50,099 --> 00:18:51,327
Is that clear?

289
00:18:53,739 --> 00:18:55,809
Mr Hawkins?

290
00:18:55,859 --> 00:18:58,737
- Yes, ma'am.
- That'll do.

291
00:18:58,779 --> 00:19:01,009
Gentlemen, this must be kept
under lock and key...

292
00:19:01,059 --> 00:19:03,653
when not in use.
And, Doctor, again...

293
00:19:03,699 --> 00:19:05,291
with the greatest
possible respect...

294
00:19:05,339 --> 00:19:07,250
zip your howling screamer.

295
00:19:07,299 --> 00:19:09,051
Captain, I assure you...

296
00:19:09,099 --> 00:19:12,296
Let me make this
as monosyllabic as possible.

297
00:19:12,339 --> 00:19:16,571
I don't much care
for this crew you hired.

298
00:19:16,619 --> 00:19:18,769
How did I describe them, Arrow?

299
00:19:18,819 --> 00:19:21,128
I said something rather good
this morning before coffee.

300
00:19:21,179 --> 00:19:25,331
"A ludicrous parcel
of drivelling galoots," ma'am.

301
00:19:25,379 --> 00:19:28,655
- There you go... poetry.
- Now, see here...

302
00:19:28,699 --> 00:19:32,738
I'd love to chat...
tea, cake, the whole shebang...

303
00:19:32,779 --> 00:19:34,098
but I have a ship to launch...

304
00:19:34,139 --> 00:19:36,016
and you've got your outfit
to buff up.

305
00:19:36,059 --> 00:19:36,179
Mr Arrow, please escort
these two neophytes...

306
00:19:36,179 --> 00:19:38,295
Mr Arrow, please escort
these two neophytes...

307
00:19:38,339 --> 00:19:39,852
down to the galley
straightaway.

308
00:19:39,899 --> 00:19:42,538
Young Hawkins will be working
for our cook, Mr Silver.

309
00:19:42,579 --> 00:19:44,774
What? The cook?

310
00:19:46,099 --> 00:19:48,454
That woman! That feline!

311
00:19:48,499 --> 00:19:50,535
Who does she think
is working for whom?

312
00:19:50,579 --> 00:19:52,888
It's my map, and
she's got me bussin' tables?

313
00:19:52,939 --> 00:19:55,499
I'll not tolerate a cross word
about our captain!

314
00:19:55,539 --> 00:20:00,135
There's no finer officer
in this or any galaxy.

315
00:20:02,619 --> 00:20:04,655
Mr Silver?

316
00:20:04,699 --> 00:20:06,690
Why, Mr Arrow, sir.

317
00:20:06,739 --> 00:20:09,094
Bringin' in such fine
and distinguished gents...

318
00:20:09,139 --> 00:20:11,095
to grace my humble galley.

319
00:20:11,139 --> 00:20:13,448
Had I known,
I'd have tucked in me shirt.

320
00:20:17,859 --> 00:20:19,736
A cyborg!

321
00:20:19,779 --> 00:20:24,170
May I introduce Dr Doppler,
the financier of our voyage?

322
00:20:24,219 --> 00:20:26,289
Love the outfit, Doc.

323
00:20:26,339 --> 00:20:29,695
Thank you. Love the eye.

324
00:20:29,739 --> 00:20:32,412
This young lad is Jim Hawkins.

325
00:20:33,539 --> 00:20:34,767
Jimbo!

326
00:20:39,419 --> 00:20:44,129
Don't be too put off
by this hunk of hardware.

327
00:20:51,619 --> 00:20:53,655
These gears have been
tough getting used to...

328
00:20:53,699 --> 00:20:57,453
but they do come in
mighty handy from time to time.

329
00:21:06,859 --> 00:21:11,808
Here, have a taste of
me famous bonzabeast stew.

330
00:21:15,699 --> 00:21:18,213
Delightfully tangy,
yet robust.

331
00:21:18,259 --> 00:21:20,568
Old family recipe.

332
00:21:21,819 --> 00:21:25,414
In fact, that was part
of the old family!

333
00:21:29,619 --> 00:21:32,338
I'm just kiddin', Doc!

334
00:21:32,379 --> 00:21:34,893
I'm nothin'
if I ain't a kidder.

335
00:21:34,939 --> 00:21:37,373
Go on, Jimbo. Have a swig.

336
00:21:44,539 --> 00:21:48,817
Morph! You jiggle-headed
blob of mischief!

337
00:21:48,859 --> 00:21:50,975
So that's
where you was hiding!

338
00:21:57,419 --> 00:21:59,808
What is that thing?

339
00:21:59,859 --> 00:22:01,531
He's a morph.

340
00:22:01,579 --> 00:22:05,891
I rescued the little
shape-shifter on Proteus 1.

341
00:22:05,939 --> 00:22:11,172
He took a shine to me.
We been together ever since.

342
00:22:11,219 --> 00:22:13,892
Right? Nice boy.

343
00:22:13,939 --> 00:22:15,213
We're about to get underway.

344
00:22:15,259 --> 00:22:17,295
Would you like to observe
the launch, Doctor?

345
00:22:17,339 --> 00:22:18,852
Would I?

346
00:22:18,899 --> 00:22:22,016
Does an active galactic nucleus
have superluminal jets?

347
00:22:22,059 --> 00:22:24,414
I'll follow you.

348
00:22:24,459 --> 00:22:29,214
Mr Hawkins will stay here
in your charge, Mr Silver.

349
00:22:29,259 --> 00:22:31,534
Beggin' your pardon, sir...

350
00:22:31,579 --> 00:22:36,209
Captain's orders! See to it
the new cabin boy's kept busy.

351
00:22:36,259 --> 00:22:38,853
- But, no, but...
- No, you can't...

352
00:22:43,059 --> 00:22:46,847
So, Captain's
put you with me, eh?

353
00:22:46,899 --> 00:22:48,776
Whatever.

354
00:22:48,819 --> 00:22:53,973
Who be a humble cyborg
to argue with a captain?

355
00:22:56,299 --> 00:22:59,177
You know... these purps...

356
00:22:59,219 --> 00:23:03,132
they're kind of like the ones
back home on Montressor.

357
00:23:03,179 --> 00:23:04,931
You ever been there?

358
00:23:04,979 --> 00:23:07,447
I can't say as I have, Jimbo.

359
00:23:08,979 --> 00:23:11,539
Come to think of it,
just before I left...

360
00:23:11,579 --> 00:23:13,535
I met this old guy...

361
00:23:13,579 --> 00:23:16,696
who was looking
for a cyborg buddy of his.

362
00:23:16,739 --> 00:23:19,412
- Is that so?
- Yeah.

363
00:23:19,459 --> 00:23:23,134
What was
that old salamander's name?

364
00:23:23,179 --> 00:23:25,454
Oh, yeah. Bones.

365
00:23:25,499 --> 00:23:27,330
Billy Bones?

366
00:23:27,379 --> 00:23:30,337
Bones? Bones?

367
00:23:30,379 --> 00:23:32,654
T'ain't ringin' any bells.

368
00:23:32,699 --> 00:23:34,769
Must have been
a different cyborg.

369
00:23:34,819 --> 00:23:38,607
There's a slew of cyborgs
roamin' this port.

370
00:23:38,659 --> 00:23:40,775
Prepare to cast off!

371
00:23:40,819 --> 00:23:44,573
Off with you, lad,
and watch the launch.

372
00:23:44,619 --> 00:23:49,056
There'll be plenty work
a-waitin' for you afterwards.

373
00:23:53,499 --> 00:23:58,653
We best be keepin' a sharp eye
on this one, eh, Morph?

374
00:23:58,699 --> 00:24:03,525
We wouldn't want him strayin'
into things he shouldn't.

375
00:24:03,525 --> 00:24:06,483
We're all clear, Captain!

376
00:24:06,525 --> 00:24:09,642
Well, my friend. Are we ready
to raise this creaking tub?

377
00:24:09,685 --> 00:24:11,721
My pleasure, Captain.

378
00:24:11,765 --> 00:24:14,677
All hands to stations!

379
00:24:15,805 --> 00:24:16,999
Smartly now!

380
00:24:17,045 --> 00:24:18,444
Come on, you scurvy scum!
I'll race you!

381
00:24:22,005 --> 00:24:25,156
Loose all solar sails!

382
00:24:30,005 --> 00:24:31,233
Come on!

383
00:24:35,885 --> 00:24:38,797
Heave up the braces.

384
00:24:38,845 --> 00:24:40,563
Brace up.

385
00:24:56,085 --> 00:24:58,679
Mr Zoff,
engage artificial gravity.

386
00:25:06,005 --> 00:25:09,281
South by southwest,
Mr Turnbuckle, heading 2-1-0-0.

387
00:25:09,325 --> 00:25:12,044
Aye, Captain. 2-1-0-0.

388
00:25:14,405 --> 00:25:16,396
Full speed, Mr Arrow,
if you please.

389
00:25:16,445 --> 00:25:17,673
Take her away!

390
00:25:21,485 --> 00:25:23,601
Brace yourself, Doctor.

391
00:26:02,925 --> 00:26:06,998
Upon my word,
an Orcus Galacticus.

392
00:26:08,605 --> 00:26:11,358
- Smile.
- Doctor, I'd stand clear...

393
00:26:16,005 --> 00:26:18,917
'Tis a grand day
for sailing, Captain...

394
00:26:18,965 --> 00:26:20,398
and look at you.

395
00:26:20,445 --> 00:26:22,913
You're as trim and as bonny
as a sloop...

396
00:26:22,965 --> 00:26:25,604
with new sails
and a fresh coat of paint.

397
00:26:25,645 --> 00:26:27,476
You can keep that kind
of flim-flammery...

398
00:26:27,525 --> 00:26:29,163
for your spaceport floozies,
Silver.

399
00:26:29,205 --> 00:26:30,684
Spaceport floozy!

400
00:26:30,725 --> 00:26:33,114
You cut me to the quick,
Captain.

401
00:26:33,165 --> 00:26:37,078
I speaks nothing
but me heart at all times.

402
00:26:37,125 --> 00:26:39,878
And, by the way,
isn't that your cabin boy...

403
00:26:39,925 --> 00:26:43,440
aimlessly footling about
in those shrouds?

404
00:26:43,485 --> 00:26:44,964
Yep, it...

405
00:26:45,005 --> 00:26:49,840
A momentary aberration, Cap'n,
soon to be addressed.

406
00:26:51,325 --> 00:26:54,078
I got two new friends
I'd like you to meet.

407
00:26:55,325 --> 00:27:00,115
Say hello to
Mr Mop and Mrs Bucket.

408
00:27:05,085 --> 00:27:06,837
Yeah, I got your Mr Mop.

409
00:27:09,925 --> 00:27:12,598
Watch it, twerp.

410
00:27:26,005 --> 00:27:28,473
What are you looking at,
weirdo?

411
00:27:29,765 --> 00:27:31,756
Yeah, weirdo.

412
00:27:35,165 --> 00:27:41,434
Cabin boys should learn
to mind their own business.

413
00:27:41,485 --> 00:27:43,953
Why? You got something to hide,
bright eyes?

414
00:27:45,405 --> 00:27:50,274
Maybe your ears
don't work so well.

415
00:27:50,325 --> 00:27:53,840
Yeah. Too bad
my nose works just fine.

416
00:27:53,885 --> 00:27:57,321
Why, you impudent little...

417
00:27:59,605 --> 00:28:03,200
Slice him! Dice him!

418
00:28:03,245 --> 00:28:07,204
Any last words, cabin boy?

419
00:28:09,325 --> 00:28:10,724
Mr Scroop...

420
00:28:13,205 --> 00:28:15,878
you ever see what happens
to a fresh purp...

421
00:28:15,925 --> 00:28:19,713
when you squeeze real hard?

422
00:28:21,765 --> 00:28:23,244
What's all this, then?

423
00:28:26,485 --> 00:28:28,282
You know the rules.

424
00:28:28,325 --> 00:28:30,919
There'll be no brawling
on this ship.

425
00:28:30,965 --> 00:28:35,675
Any further offenders
will be confined to the brig...

426
00:28:35,725 --> 00:28:38,319
for the remainder
of the voyage.

427
00:28:38,365 --> 00:28:41,755
Am I clear, Mr Scroop?

428
00:28:47,405 --> 00:28:49,600
Transparently.

429
00:28:54,925 --> 00:28:57,564
Well done, Mr Arrow, sir!

430
00:28:57,605 --> 00:29:00,358
A tight ship's
a happy ship, sir.

431
00:29:01,485 --> 00:29:04,079
Jimbo, I gave you a job.

432
00:29:04,125 --> 00:29:06,480
I was doing it
until that bug thing...

433
00:29:06,525 --> 00:29:11,440
Belay that! I want
this deck swabbed spotless...

434
00:29:11,485 --> 00:29:14,875
and heaven help you if
I come back and it's not done.

435
00:29:14,925 --> 00:29:18,440
Morph?
Keep an eye on this pup...

436
00:29:18,485 --> 00:29:21,716
and let me know if there be
any more distractions.

437
00:29:30,805 --> 00:29:33,114
So, we're all here, then.

438
00:29:33,165 --> 00:29:36,237
- Excuse me.
- Fine.

439
00:29:36,285 --> 00:29:42,394
Now, if you pardon
my plain speaking, gentlemen...

440
00:29:42,445 --> 00:29:44,083
are you all...

441
00:29:44,125 --> 00:29:48,835
stark-raving,
totally blinking daft?

442
00:29:48,885 --> 00:29:51,115
After all me finagling
getting us hired...

443
00:29:51,165 --> 00:29:52,678
as an upstanding crew...

444
00:29:52,725 --> 00:29:56,479
you want to blow the whole
mutiny before it's time?

445
00:29:56,525 --> 00:29:59,323
The boy was sniffing about.

446
00:29:59,365 --> 00:30:04,678
You just stick to the plan,
you bug-brained twit.

447
00:30:04,725 --> 00:30:08,195
As for the boy,
I'll run him so ragged...

448
00:30:08,245 --> 00:30:10,236
he won't have time to think.

449
00:30:20,485 --> 00:30:22,953
This has been a fun day, huh?

450
00:30:23,005 --> 00:30:27,237
Making new friends
like that spider psycho.

451
00:30:27,285 --> 00:30:29,162
Spider psycho!

452
00:30:29,205 --> 00:30:31,002
A little uglier.

453
00:30:33,325 --> 00:30:34,519
Pretty close.

454
00:30:34,565 --> 00:30:38,717
Thank heavens
for little miracles.

455
00:30:38,765 --> 00:30:40,244
Up here for an hour...

456
00:30:40,285 --> 00:30:42,515
and the deck's
still in one piece.

457
00:30:42,565 --> 00:30:45,523
Look, I...

458
00:30:47,445 --> 00:30:48,673
What you did...

459
00:30:50,885 --> 00:30:52,204
Thanks.

460
00:30:54,125 --> 00:30:56,002
Didn't your pap
ever teach you...

461
00:30:56,045 --> 00:30:58,115
to pick your fights
a bit more carefully?

462
00:31:03,165 --> 00:31:05,554
Your father's
not the teachin' sort.

463
00:31:05,605 --> 00:31:11,362
No. He was more the taking off
and never coming back sort.

464
00:31:16,085 --> 00:31:17,359
Sorry, lad.

465
00:31:17,405 --> 00:31:20,954
No big deal.
I'm doing just fine.

466
00:31:21,005 --> 00:31:24,441
Is that so?

467
00:31:24,485 --> 00:31:27,921
Since the captain
has put you in my charge...

468
00:31:27,965 --> 00:31:30,035
like it or not,
I'll be pounding a few skills...

469
00:31:30,085 --> 00:31:32,440
into that thick head of yours
to keep you out of trouble.

470
00:31:32,485 --> 00:31:33,679
- What?
- From now on...

471
00:31:33,725 --> 00:31:35,920
I'm not letting you
out of me sight.

472
00:31:35,965 --> 00:31:37,159
You can't do...

473
00:31:37,205 --> 00:31:38,684
You won't so much
as eat, sleep...

474
00:31:38,725 --> 00:31:41,797
or scratch your bum
without my say-so.

475
00:31:41,845 --> 00:31:43,164
Don't do me any favours!

476
00:31:43,205 --> 00:31:45,878
You can be sure of that,
my lad.

477
00:31:45,925 --> 00:31:46,031
You can be sure of that.

478
00:31:46,031 --> 00:31:48,465
You can be sure of that.

479
00:31:53,671 --> 00:31:56,139
Put some elbow into it.

480
00:32:06,391 --> 00:32:10,623
I am a question to the world

481
00:32:10,671 --> 00:32:13,708
Not an answer to be heard

482
00:32:13,751 --> 00:32:18,586
Or a moment
that's held in your arms

483
00:32:18,631 --> 00:32:23,102
And what do you think
you'd ever say

484
00:32:23,151 --> 00:32:26,143
I won't listen anyway

485
00:32:26,191 --> 00:32:27,863
You don't know me

486
00:32:27,911 --> 00:32:30,550
And I'll never be what you want

487
00:32:30,591 --> 00:32:32,946
Me to be

488
00:32:37,311 --> 00:32:41,668
And what do you think
you'd understand?

489
00:32:41,711 --> 00:32:44,828
I'm a boy, no, I'm a man

490
00:32:44,871 --> 00:32:49,581
You can take me
and throw me away

491
00:32:49,631 --> 00:32:54,182
And how can you learn
what's never shown

492
00:32:54,231 --> 00:32:57,143
Yeah, you stand here
on your own

493
00:32:57,191 --> 00:32:58,783
They don't know me

494
00:32:58,831 --> 00:33:03,985
'Cause I'm not here

495
00:33:04,031 --> 00:33:07,785
And I want a moment to be real

496
00:33:07,831 --> 00:33:11,267
Want to touch things
I don't feel

497
00:33:11,311 --> 00:33:16,101
Want to hold on
and feel I belong

498
00:33:16,151 --> 00:33:20,622
And how can the world
want me to change

499
00:33:20,671 --> 00:33:23,629
They're the ones
that stay the same

500
00:33:23,671 --> 00:33:25,627
They don't know me

501
00:33:25,671 --> 00:33:29,903
But I'm still here

502
00:33:29,951 --> 00:33:34,581
And you see the things
they never see

503
00:33:34,631 --> 00:33:37,782
All you wanted, I could be

504
00:33:37,831 --> 00:33:39,344
Now you know me

505
00:33:39,391 --> 00:33:42,064
And I'm not afraid

506
00:33:42,111 --> 00:33:46,946
And I want to tell you who I am

507
00:33:46,991 --> 00:33:50,063
Can you help me be a man?

508
00:33:50,111 --> 00:33:51,590
They can't break me

509
00:33:51,631 --> 00:33:55,829
As long as I know who I am

510
00:33:58,031 --> 00:34:01,148
They can't tell me who to be

511
00:34:04,311 --> 00:34:08,782
'Cause I'm not what they see

512
00:34:08,831 --> 00:34:10,708
Yeah, the world
