It's back on the ship?

711
00:52:23,172 --> 00:52:26,448
Stifle that blob and get low.

712
00:52:28,012 --> 00:52:30,242
We've got company.

713
00:52:34,732 --> 00:52:37,451
We need
a more defensible position.

714
00:52:37,492 --> 00:52:39,483
Mr Hawkins, scout ahead.

715
00:52:41,212 --> 00:52:42,361
Aye, Captain.

716
00:52:42,412 --> 00:52:45,006
Steady, steady.

717
00:52:45,052 --> 00:52:48,089
Now, let's have a look at that.

718
00:53:26,802 --> 00:53:28,440
This is fantastic!

719
00:53:28,482 --> 00:53:31,315
A carbon-based life form
come to rescue me at last!

720
00:53:31,362 --> 00:53:33,318
I just want to hug you
and squeeze you...

721
00:53:33,362 --> 00:53:34,841
and hold you close to me.

722
00:53:34,882 --> 00:53:38,033
Alright. OK.
Would you let go of me?

723
00:53:38,082 --> 00:53:39,720
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

724
00:53:39,762 --> 00:53:43,311
It's just I've been marooned
for so long.

725
00:53:43,362 --> 00:53:45,830
Solitude's fine.
Don't get me wrong.

726
00:53:45,882 --> 00:53:47,600
For heaven's sakes,
after a hundred years...

727
00:53:47,642 --> 00:53:51,112
you go a little nuts!

728
00:53:51,162 --> 00:53:52,880
I'm sorry. Am I...

729
00:53:52,922 --> 00:53:54,275
I am...

730
00:53:54,322 --> 00:53:57,712
My name is...

731
00:54:01,802 --> 00:54:04,157
B.E.N.!
Of course, I'm B. E. N.

732
00:54:04,202 --> 00:54:06,762
Bioelectronic Navigator.
Oops.

733
00:54:06,802 --> 00:54:08,281
- And you are?
- Jim.

734
00:54:08,322 --> 00:54:09,880
What a pleasure
to meet you, Jimmy.

735
00:54:09,922 --> 00:54:11,833
- It's Jim.
- Anyway...

736
00:54:11,882 --> 00:54:13,440
Look, I'm in a hurry.

737
00:54:13,482 --> 00:54:15,916
I got to find a place to hide.
There's pirates chasing me.

738
00:54:15,962 --> 00:54:19,034
Pirates!
Don't get me started on pirates!

739
00:54:19,082 --> 00:54:22,040
I don't like them.
I remember Captain Flint.

740
00:54:22,082 --> 00:54:24,312
This guy had such a temper.

741
00:54:24,362 --> 00:54:26,398
Wait, wait, wait.
You knew Captain Flint?

742
00:54:26,442 --> 00:54:29,240
I think he suffered
from mood swings, personally.

743
00:54:29,282 --> 00:54:30,920
I'm not a therapist,
and anyway...

744
00:54:30,962 --> 00:54:32,998
You let me know
when I'm rambling.

745
00:54:33,042 --> 00:54:34,361
But that means...

746
00:54:34,402 --> 00:54:36,597
But then you gotta know
about the treasure?

747
00:54:36,642 --> 00:54:38,155
- Treasure?
- Flint's trove?

748
00:54:38,202 --> 00:54:40,079
You know,
loot of a thousand worlds.

749
00:54:40,122 --> 00:54:41,953
It's... Well, it's...

750
00:54:42,002 --> 00:54:45,472
It's all a little...
little fuzzy.

751
00:54:45,522 --> 00:54:48,958
Wait. I remember.

752
00:54:49,002 --> 00:54:50,993
I do. Treasure!

753
00:54:51,042 --> 00:54:53,795
Lots of treasure
buried in the centroid...

754
00:54:53,842 --> 00:54:55,798
centroid of the mechanism.

755
00:54:55,842 --> 00:55:00,791
There was this big door
opening and closing...

756
00:55:00,842 --> 00:55:02,514
