get to his treasure...

758
00:55:04,042 --> 00:55:05,794
so I helped him...

759
00:55:08,162 --> 00:55:11,518
Data inaccessible!
Reboot!

760
00:55:11,562 --> 00:55:14,156
Reboot! And you are?

761
00:55:14,202 --> 00:55:15,396
What about the treasure?

762
00:55:15,442 --> 00:55:16,875
I want to say Larry.

763
00:55:16,922 --> 00:55:19,038
The centroid
of the mechanism, or...

764
00:55:19,082 --> 00:55:22,122
I'm sorry. My memory
isn't what it used to be.

765
00:55:22,122 --> 00:55:25,000
I've lost my mind.

766
00:55:25,042 --> 00:55:26,475
You haven't found it, have you?

767
00:55:26,522 --> 00:55:29,992
My missing piece?
My primary memory circuit?

768
00:55:30,042 --> 00:55:34,513
Look, B.E.N., I really need
to find a place to hide.

769
00:55:34,562 --> 00:55:38,396
So I'm gonna be moving on.

770
00:55:38,442 --> 00:55:41,673
Oh, so, well, then...

771
00:55:41,722 --> 00:55:45,397
I guess
this is good-bye, huh?

772
00:55:45,442 --> 00:55:50,197
I'm sorry that
I'm so dysfunctional.

773
00:55:50,242 --> 00:55:55,077
So, go ahead.
I do understand.

774
00:55:55,122 --> 00:55:58,353
I do. Bye-bye.

775
00:56:01,922 --> 00:56:05,437
If you're gonna come along,
you have to stop talking.

776
00:56:05,482 --> 00:56:09,031
Huzzah!
This is fantastic!

777
00:56:09,082 --> 00:56:12,154
Me and my best buddy
are lookin' for a...

778
00:56:14,122 --> 00:56:15,874
Being quiet.

779
00:56:15,922 --> 00:56:18,197
And you have to stop
touching me.

780
00:56:18,242 --> 00:56:21,678
Touching and talking.
My two big no-nos.

781
00:56:21,722 --> 00:56:23,713
OK. I think we should...

782
00:56:23,762 --> 00:56:26,754
Say, before we go out
on our big search...

783
00:56:26,802 --> 00:56:31,114
would you mind if we made
a quick pit stop at my place?

784
00:56:31,162 --> 00:56:33,039
Kind of urgent.

785
00:56:33,082 --> 00:56:36,438
B.E.N., I think
you just solved my problem.

786
00:56:40,402 --> 00:56:42,313
Pardon the mess, people.

787
00:56:42,362 --> 00:56:43,681
You'd think
in a hundred years...

788
00:56:43,722 --> 00:56:45,235
I would've dusted
a little more often...

789
00:56:45,282 --> 00:56:47,432
but when you're batchin' it...

790
00:56:47,482 --> 00:56:50,042
you tend to let things go.

791
00:56:50,082 --> 00:56:52,232
Isn't that sweet?

792
00:56:52,282 --> 00:56:55,274
I find old-fashioned romance
so touching, don't you?

793
00:56:55,322 --> 00:56:58,041
How about drinks
for the happy couple?

794
00:56:59,762 --> 00:57:03,232
Thank you, we don't drink...
and we're not a couple.

795
00:57:05,322 --> 00:57:07,552
Look at these markings.

796
00:57:07,602 --> 00:57:10,878
They're identical
to the ones on the map.

797
00:57:10,922 --> 00:57:12,958
I suspect these are
the hieroglyphic remnants...

798
00:57:13,002 --> 00:57:14,640
of an ancient culture.

799
00:57:14,682 --> 00:57:18,675
Mr Hawkins, stop anyone
who tries to approach.

800
00:57:18,722 --> 00:57:20,474
Yes, yes.
Now listen to me...

801
00:57:20,522 --> 00:57:24,595
stop giving orders for a few
milliseconds and lie still.

802
00:57:24,642 --> 00:57:26,678
Very forceful, Doctor.

803
00:57:26,722 --> 00:57:28,599
Go on. Say something else.

804
00:57:28,642 --> 00:57:31,793
Look! There's some more
of your buddies!

805
00:57:31,842 --> 00:57:34,675
Hey, fellas!
We're over here, fellas!

806
00:57:39,802 --> 00:57:43,715
Stop wastin' your fire!

807
00:57:43,762 --> 00:57:47,152
Hello, up there!

808
00:57:51,242 --> 00:57:54,552
If it's alright
with the captain...

809
00:57:54,602 --> 00:57:57,241
I'd like a short word with ya.

810
00:57:57,282 --> 00:58:00,638
No tricks,
just a little palaver.

811
00:58:00,682 --> 00:58:00,762
Come to bargain for the map,
doubtless.

812
00:58:00,762 --> 00:58:03,196
Come to bargain for the map,
doubtless.

813
00:58:03,242 --> 00:58:06,393
- Pestilential...
- Captain.

814
00:58:06,442 --> 00:58:11,721
That means... that he thinks
we still have it.

815
00:58:16,402 --> 00:58:21,351
Morphy!
I wondered where you was off to.

816
00:58:26,762 --> 00:58:29,913
This poor old leg's
downright snarky...

817
00:58:29,962 --> 00:58:32,840
since that game attack
we had in the galley.

818
00:58:38,442 --> 00:58:41,240
Whatever you heard
back there...

819
00:58:41,282 --> 00:58:43,318
at least the part
concerning you...

820
00:58:43,362 --> 00:58:47,150
I didn't mean a word of it.

821
00:58:47,202 --> 00:58:51,036
Had that bloodthirsty lot
thought I'd gone soft...

822
00:58:51,082 --> 00:58:53,516
they'd have gutted us both.

823
00:58:55,562 --> 00:58:59,840
Listen to me.
If we play our cards right...

824
00:58:59,882 --> 00:59:05,400
we can both walk away
from this rich as kings.

825
00:59:07,362 --> 00:59:10,320
You get me that map...

826
00:59:10,362 --> 00:59:12,114
and...

827
00:59:12,162 --> 00:59:17,441
an even portion
of the treasure is yours.

828
00:59:21,842 --> 00:59:24,151
Boy.

829
00:59:24,202 --> 00:59:26,670
You are really something.

830
00:59:26,722 --> 00:59:29,361
All that talk of greatness...

831
00:59:29,402 --> 00:59:32,872
light coming off my sails...
what a joke.

832
00:59:32,922 --> 00:59:34,674
Just see here, Jimbo...

833
00:59:34,722 --> 00:59:35,916
At least
you taught me one thing.

834
00:59:35,962 --> 00:59:37,156
Stick to it, right?

835
00:59:37,202 --> 00:59:39,079
That's just what I'm gonna do.

836
00:59:39,122 --> 00:59:43,274
I'll make sure you never see
one drabloon of my treasure!

837
00:59:43,322 --> 00:59:46,632
That treasure is owed me,
by thunder!

838
00:59:46,682 --> 00:59:50,914
Try to find it without my map,
by thunder!

839
00:59:50,962 --> 00:59:55,877
You still don't know how
to pick your fights, do you?

840
00:59:55,922 --> 00:59:59,073
Now, mark me.

841
00:59:59,122 --> 01:00:02,751
Either I get that map
by dawn tomorrow...

842
01:00:02,802 --> 01:00:06,761
or so help me,
I'll use the ship's cannons...

843
01:00:06,802 --> 01:00:10,397
to blast ya all
to kingdom come!

844
01:00:10,442 --> 01:00:13,354
Morph, hop to it.

845
01:00:14,562 --> 01:00:16,041
Now!

846
01:00:18,442 --> 01:00:20,239
Blast it!

847
01:00:31,442 --> 01:00:33,114
Gentlemen...

848
01:00:33,162 --> 01:00:38,680
we must stay together and...

849
01:00:38,722 --> 01:00:40,394
And what? What?

850
01:00:40,442 --> 01:00:42,956
We must stay together
and what?

851
01:00:43,002 --> 01:00:48,201
Doctor,
you have wonderful eyes.

852
01:00:48,242 --> 01:00:49,721
She's lost her mind!

853
01:00:49,762 --> 01:00:51,036
You gotta help her.

854
01:00:51,082 --> 01:00:53,277
Dang it, Jim. I'm an astronomer,
not a doctor.

855
01:00:53,322 --> 01:00:55,677
I am a doctor,
but not that kind of doctor.

856
01:00:55,722 --> 01:00:57,201
I have a doctorate.
It's not the same thing.

857
01:00:57,242 --> 01:00:58,561
You can't help people
with a doctorate.

858
01:00:58,602 --> 01:01:01,116
You just sit there,
and you're useless.

859
01:01:01,162 --> 01:01:03,357
It's OK, Doc.

860
01:01:03,402 --> 01:01:05,040
It's alright.

861
01:01:05,082 --> 01:01:08,199
Yeah, Doc! Jimmy knows exactly
how to get out of this.

862
01:01:08,242 --> 01:01:11,279
Jimmy has this knowledge
of things.

863
01:01:11,322 --> 01:01:11,466
Any thoughts at all?

864
01:01:11,466 --> 01:01:14,856
Any thoughts at all?

865
01:01:14,906 --> 01:01:17,784
Without the map, we're dead.

866
01:01:18,866 --> 01:01:21,585
If we try to leave, we're dead.

867
01:01:21,626 --> 01:01:24,743
- Lf we stay here...
- We're dead!

868
01:01:29,146 --> 01:01:33,503
I think that Jimmy could
use a little quiet time.

869
01:01:33,546 --> 01:01:36,697
So I'll just slip out
the back door.

870
01:01:36,746 --> 01:01:38,862
- Back door?
- Oh, yeah.

871
01:01:38,906 --> 01:01:40,862
I get this delightful breeze
through here...

872
01:01:40,906 --> 01:01:43,625
which I think is important,
because ventilation...

873
01:01:43,666 --> 01:01:46,021
What is all this stuff?

874
01:01:46,066 --> 01:01:48,296
You mean the miles and miles
of machinery that run...

875
01:01:48,346 --> 01:01:50,337
through the entire course
of the inside of this planet?

876
01:01:50,386 --> 01:01:52,138
Not a clue.

877
01:01:52,186 --> 01:01:54,336
Doc! I think I found
a way out of here!

878
01:01:54,386 --> 01:01:56,820
No, no. Jim, wait.
The captain ordered us to stay...

879
01:01:56,866 --> 01:01:59,664
- I'll be back.
- Cannonball!

880
01:02:09,066 --> 01:02:11,500
- What's the plan?
- B.E.N., quiet.

881
01:02:15,386 --> 01:02:16,944
Here it is.

882
01:02:16,986 --> 01:02:20,103
We sneak back to the Legacy,
disable the laser cannons...

883
01:02:20,146 --> 01:02:21,864
and bring back the map.

884
01:02:21,906 --> 01:02:23,862
That's a good plan.
I like that plan.

885
01:02:23,906 --> 01:02:26,864
The only thing is,
how do we get there?

886
01:02:26,906 --> 01:02:28,385
On that.

887
01:02:40,506 --> 01:02:43,464
Sorry, sorry.

888
01:02:49,706 --> 01:02:52,174
I'll get the map.
You wait here.

889
01:02:52,226 --> 01:02:55,662
Roger, Jimmy. I'll neutralise
laser cannons, sir!

890
01:02:55,706 --> 01:02:59,460
Yo-ho, yo-ho,
a pirate's life for me

891
01:03:01,266 --> 01:03:05,054
Disable a few laser cannons.
What is the big deal?

892
01:03:05,106 --> 01:03:08,621
All we gotta do is find
that one little wire.

893
01:03:08,666 --> 01:03:11,100
Oh, mama.

894
01:03:18,946 --> 01:03:21,779
Bad, B.E.N. Bad. Fixing!

895
01:03:21,826 --> 01:03:24,499
That stupid robot's
gonna get us all... killed.

896
01:03:24,546 --> 01:03:26,741
Cabin boy.

897
01:03:53,986 --> 01:03:55,624
Don't panic.

898
01:03:55,666 --> 01:03:57,543
Breathing in,
breathing out...

899
01:04:18,066 --> 01:04:19,624
This has gotta be cannons.

900
01:04:20,826 --> 01:04:22,225
Maybe not.

901
01:04:43,986 --> 01:04:45,863
Come on, come on.

902
01:04:45,906 --> 01:04:50,024
- No!
- Oh, yes.

903
01:04:50,066 --> 01:04:53,103
Do say hello to Mr Arrow.

904
01:04:56,586 --> 01:04:58,338
Tell him yourself!

905
01:05:07,786 --> 01:05:10,823
Back you go, you naughty plug!

906
01:05:21,746 --> 01:05:24,943
Laser cannons disconnected,
Captain Jimmy, sir!

907
01:05:24,986 --> 01:05:27,022
That wasn't so tough.

908
01:05:34,506 --> 01:05:36,497
Doc, wake up!

909
01:05:36,546 --> 01:05:39,663
I got the map.

910
01:05:39,706 --> 01:05:44,734
Fine work, Jimbo.
Fine work indeed.

911
01:05:48,746 --> 01:05:51,385
Thanks for
showing us the way, boy.

912
01:05:59,146 --> 01:06:01,455
What's this sorry stack
of metal?

913
01:06:01,506 --> 01:06:02,700
Not the face!

914
01:06:02,746 --> 01:06:05,544
You're just like me, Jimbo.

915
01:06:05,586 --> 01:06:08,464
Ya hates to lose.

916
01:06:16,666 --> 01:06:18,975
What the devil's the...

917
01:06:22,866 --> 01:06:24,379
Open it.

918
01:06:32,706 --> 01:06:34,936
I'd get busy.

919
01:06:50,866 --> 01:06:54,381
The powers that be.
Would you look?

920
01:07:00,546 --> 01:07:04,380
Tie him up and leave him
with the others till we...

921
01:07:05,386 --> 01:07:06,944
You want the map...

922
01:07:06,986 --> 01:07:08,783
you're taking me, too.

923
01:07:16,506 --> 01:07:18,224
We'll take 'em all.

924
01:07:39,586 --> 01:07:42,225
It's OK, Morph.

925
01:07:42,266 --> 01:07:44,063
Jimmy,
I don't know about you...

926
01:07:44,106 --> 01:07:47,735
but I'm starting to see my life
pass in front of my eyes.

927
01:07:47,786 --> 01:07:49,697
At least, I think it's my life.

928
01:07:49,746 --> 01:07:52,783
Was I ever dancing
with an android named Lupe?

929
01:07:52,826 --> 01:07:56,819
B.E.N., shh.
This isn't over yet.

930
01:07:58,026 --> 01:08:00,494
We're gettin' close, lads.

931
01:08:00,546 --> 01:08:03,856
I smell treasure a-waitin'.

932
01:08:09,746 --> 01:08:11,782
Where is it?

933
01:08:11,826 --> 01:08:16,058
I see nothing! One great, big
stinking hunk of nothing!

934
01:08:16,106 --> 01:08:18,859
What's going on, Jimbo?

935
01:08:18,906 --> 01:08:21,739
I don't know.
I can't get it open.

936
01:08:21,786 --> 01:08:24,778
We should've never
followed this boy!

937
01:08:24,826 --> 01:08:29,456
I'd suggest you get that gizmo
going again, and fast!

938
01:08:29,506 --> 01:08:32,737
Let's rip his gizzard
right out right now!

939
01:08:32,786 --> 01:08:35,220
Throw him off the cliff!

940
01:08:55,466 --> 01:08:57,821
Have mercy.

941
01:08:59,186 --> 01:09:01,416
The Lagoon Nebula?

942
01:09:01,466 --> 01:09:04,936
But that's halfway
across the galaxy.

943
01:09:06,586 --> 01:09:08,895
A big door...

944
01:09:08,946 --> 01:09:11,016
opening and closing.

945
01:09:14,746 --> 01:09:16,418
Let's see.

946
01:09:16,466 --> 01:09:19,902
Kinapis.

947
01:09:19,946 --> 01:09:21,425
Montressor spaceport.

948
01:09:24,546 --> 01:09:26,423
So that's how Flint did it.

949
01:09:26,466 --> 01:09:31,460
He used this portal to roam
the universe stealing treasure.

950
01:09:31,506 --> 01:09:33,701
But where'd he stash it all?

951
01:09:34,946 --> 01:09:38,018
Where's that blasted treasure?

952
01:09:38,066 --> 01:09:40,182
Treasure! Treasure!

953
01:09:40,226 --> 01:09:42,137
It's buried in the...

954
01:09:42,186 --> 01:09:46,179
Buried in the centroid
of the mechanism.

955
01:09:46,226 --> 01:09:49,935
What if the whole planet
is the mechanism...

956
01:09:49,986 --> 01:09:53,535
and the treasure is buried
in the centre of this planet?

957
01:09:57,666 --> 01:10:00,499
How in blue blazes
are we supposed to get there?

958
01:10:00,546 --> 01:10:03,902
Just open the right door.

959
01:10:19,826 --> 01:10:23,057
Wait for me!

960
01:10:31,386 --> 01:10:35,698
The loot of a thousand worlds.

961
01:10:38,506 --> 01:10:42,021
We are going to need
a bigger boat!

962
01:10:53,426 --> 01:10:56,623
This is all seeming
very familiar.

963
01:10:58,586 --> 01:11:01,658
I can't remember why.

964
01:11:01,706 --> 01:11:03,298
B.E.N., come on.

965
01:11:03,346 --> 01:11:05,701
We're getting out of here, and
we're not leaving empty-handed.

966
01:11:05,746 --> 01:11:07,782
But, Jimmy!

967
01:11:09,226 --> 01:11:12,616
A lifetime of searching.

968
01:11:12,666 --> 01:11:15,624
And at long last...

969
01:11:16,706 --> 01:11:19,300
I can touch it.

970
01:11:19,346 --> 01:11:20,745
Do you know what's strange?

971
01:11:20,786 --> 01:11:22,378
I can't tell you
how frustrating this is.

972
01:11:22,426 --> 01:11:23,939
There's something just...

973
01:11:23,986 --> 01:11:26,136
It's nagging
at the back of my mind.

974
01:11:27,666 --> 01:11:30,897
- Captain Flint?
- In the flesh!

975
01:11:30,946 --> 01:11:34,541
Sort of.
Except for skin, organs...

976
01:11:34,586 --> 01:11:37,339
or anything
that resembles flesh...

977
01:11:37,386 --> 01:11:39,263
that's not there.

978
01:11:39,306 --> 01:11:41,183
And yet it's so odd?

979
01:11:41,226 --> 01:11:44,104
I remember there was
something horrible...

980
01:11:44,146 --> 01:11:46,137
Flint didn't want
anyone else to know...

981
01:11:46,186 --> 01:11:50,020
but I just can't remember
what it was.

982
01:11:50,066 --> 01:11:53,695
A mind is a terrible thing
to lose!

983
01:11:55,466 --> 01:11:59,425
I think I found your mind.
Hold still.

984
01:11:59,466 --> 01:12:02,139
Your hands are very, very cold.

985
01:12:07,266 --> 01:12:09,905
You know, Jimmy,
I was just thinking...

986
01:12:09,946 --> 01:12:12,255
I was just think...

987
01:12:12,306 --> 01:12:15,218
It's all flooding back!
All my memories!

988
01:12:15,266 --> 01:12:16,858
Right up until Flint
pulled my memory circuits...

989
01:12:16,906 --> 01:12:20,694
so I could never tell anybody
about his booby trap!

990
01:12:20,746 --> 01:12:22,145
Speaking of which...

991
01:12:25,666 --> 01:12:28,180
Flint wanted to make sure that
nobody stole his treasure...

992
01:12:28,226 --> 01:12:29,545
so he rigged
this whole planet...

993
01:12:29,586 --> 01:12:32,578
to blow higher
than a Kalepsian kite!

994
01:12:42,866 --> 01:12:44,663
Run, Jimmy!
Run for your life!

995
01:12:44,706 --> 01:12:46,298
Go back and help
the captain and Doc!

996
01:12:46,346 --> 01:12:49,383
If I'm not there in 5 minutes,
leave without me.

997
01:12:49,426 --> 01:12:52,498
I am not leaving my buddy Jimmy.

998
01:12:52,546 --> 01:12:55,106
Unless he looks at me
like that.

999
01:13:16,626 --> 01:13:19,220
Come back here, ya blighters!

1000
01:13:34,106 --> 01:13:39,055
All my life, I dreamed of
an adventure like this.

1001
01:13:39,106 --> 01:13:43,224
I'm just sorry I couldn't
have been more helpful.

1002
01:13:43,266 --> 01:13:45,143
Don't be daft.

1003
01:13:45,186 --> 01:13:48,735
You've been very helpful.
Truly.

1004
01:13:48,786 --> 01:13:52,699
I feel like such
a useless weakling...

1005
01:13:53,986 --> 01:13:56,375
with abnormally thin wrists.

1006
01:13:56,426 --> 01:13:59,577
Excuse me, brutish pirate.

1007
01:13:59,626 --> 01:14:01,298
Yes, you. I have a question.

1008
01:14:01,346 --> 01:14:03,541
Is it that your body
is too massive...

1009
01:14:03,586 --> 01:14:05,019
for your teeny-tiny head...

1010
01:14:05,066 --> 01:14:07,421
or is it that your head
is too teeny-tiny...

1011
01:14:07,466 --> 01:14:10,185
for your big, fat body?

1012
01:14:10,226 --> 01:14:12,262
I pummel you good!

1013
01:14:12,306 --> 01:14:14,536
I'm sure you will,
but before you do...

1014
01:14:14,586 --> 01:14:17,578
I have one more question.
Is this yours?

1015
01:14:25,266 --> 01:14:28,338
Yes!
Morph, we are so out of here!

1016
01:14:31,466 --> 01:14:35,095
Aren't you the seventh wonder
of the universe?

1017
01:14:35,146 --> 01:14:37,580
Get back!

1018
01:14:41,506 --> 01:14:45,260
I like you, lad,
but I've come too far...

1019
01:14:45,306 --> 01:14:48,457
to let you stand
between me and me treasure.

1020
01:15:06,626 --> 01:15:09,345
Oh, no, you don't!

1021
01:15:17,546 --> 01:15:18,820
What?

1022
01:15:26,746 --> 01:15:28,816
Reach for me now!

1023
01:15:28,866 --> 01:15:31,699
Reach!

1024
01:15:31,746 --> 01:15:33,384
I can't!

1025
01:15:48,946 --> 01:15:52,302
Blast me for a fool!

1026
01:16:14,562 --> 01:16:16,439
Silver, you gave up?

1027
01:16:16,482 --> 01:16:20,157
Just a lifelong obsession, Jim.
I'll get over it.

1028
01:16:20,202 --> 01:16:21,920
Aloha, Jimmy!

1029
01:16:24,162 --> 01:16:25,914
Hurry, people!
We got exactly two minutes...

1030
01:16:25,962 --> 01:16:28,840
and thirty-four seconds
till planet's destruction!

1031
01:16:28,882 --> 01:16:32,192
You're doing fine, Doctor.
Ease her over gently.

1032
01:16:34,642 --> 01:16:37,554
We were better off
on exploding planet!

1033
01:16:39,802 --> 01:16:41,554
Take us out of here, metal man!

1034
01:16:41,602 --> 01:16:43,115
Aye, Captain!

1035
01:16:46,522 --> 01:16:49,241
Captain, you dropped from
the heavens in the nick of...

1036
01:16:49,282 --> 01:16:51,955
Save your claptrap
for the judge, Silver!

1037
01:17:01,882 --> 01:17:03,440
Mizzen sail demobilised,
Captain!

1038
01:17:03,482 --> 01:17:05,313
Thrusters at only
thirty percent of capacity.

1039
01:17:05,362 --> 01:17:07,193
Thirty percent?
That means...

1040
01:17:07,242 --> 01:17:10,154
We'll never clear
the planet's explosion in time.

1041
01:17:17,722 --> 01:17:20,475
- We gotta turn around.
- What?

1042
01:17:20,522 --> 01:17:23,275
There's a portal back there.
It can get us out of here!

1043
01:17:23,322 --> 01:17:25,472
Pardon me, Jim,
but didn't that portal open...

1044
01:17:25,522 --> 01:17:27,558
onto a raging inferno?

1045
01:17:27,602 --> 01:17:30,435
Yes, but I'm gonna change that.

1046
01:17:30,482 --> 01:17:34,270
I'm gonna open
a different door.

1047
01:17:34,322 --> 01:17:35,596
Captain, really, I don't see
how this is possible...

1048
01:17:35,642 --> 01:17:37,758
Listen to the boy!

1049
01:17:37,802 --> 01:17:40,157
One minute, twenty-nine seconds
till planet's destruction!

1050
01:17:40,202 --> 01:17:43,672
- What do you need, Jim?
- Some way to attach this.

1051
01:17:43,722 --> 01:17:45,997
Alright. Stand back, now.

1052
01:17:47,562 --> 01:17:50,952
- There you go.
- There you go.

1053
01:17:52,042 --> 01:17:54,237
No matter what happens...

1054
01:17:54,282 --> 01:17:56,716
keep the ship heading
straight for that portal.

1055
01:17:56,762 --> 01:17:59,481
Fifty-eight seconds!

1056
01:18:06,042 --> 01:18:08,033
You heard him!

1057
01:18:08,082 --> 01:18:11,313
Get this blasted heap
turned 'round!

1058
01:18:11,362 --> 01:18:13,751
Doctor,
head us back to the portal.

1059
01:18:13,802 --> 01:18:15,201
Aye, Captain.

1060
01:18:36,762 --> 01:18:38,400
Go to the right!

1061
01:18:38,442 --> 01:18:41,991
I know, I know!
Will you let me drive?

1062
01:18:44,162 --> 01:18:45,993
Twenty-five seconds!

1063
01:18:55,402 --> 01:18:57,074
Come on, lad.

1064
01:18:58,522 --> 01:19:01,275
Seventeen seconds!

1065
01:19:15,682 --> 01:19:19,834
Seven... six... five... four...

1066
01:19:19,882 --> 01:19:22,396
three... two...

1067
01:19:33,362 --> 01:19:35,876
You done it, Jimmy!

1068
01:19:35,922 --> 01:19:38,072
You done it, boy!

1069
01:19:39,402 --> 01:19:41,870
Didn't I say the lad
had greatness in him?

1070
01:19:53,682 --> 01:19:57,152
Unorthodox,
but ludicrously effective.

1071
01:19:57,202 --> 01:19:58,954
I'd be proud
to recommend you...

1072
01:19:59,002 --> 01:20:02,677
to the Interstellar Academy.
They could use a man like you.

1073
01:20:02,722 --> 01:20:05,520
Wait until your mother
hears about this!

1074
01:20:05,562 --> 01:20:07,553
We may downplay
the life-threatening parts.

1075
01:20:07,602 --> 01:20:11,390
Jimmy,
that was unforgettable!

1076
01:20:11,442 --> 01:20:12,841
I know you don't like
touching...

1077
01:20:12,882 --> 01:20:15,760
but get ready for a hug,
big guy!

1078
01:20:18,842 --> 01:20:20,958
You hugged me back.

1079
01:20:21,002 --> 01:20:23,914
I promised myself
I wouldn't cry.

1080
01:20:29,642 --> 01:20:31,553
Does anyone have a tissue?

1081
01:20:33,948 --> 01:20:37,020
- Morphy, we gotta make tracks.
- I know.

1082
01:20:37,068 --> 01:20:39,184
You never quit, do you?

1083
01:20:42,028 --> 01:20:44,019
I was merely
checking to make sure...

1084
01:20:44,068 --> 01:20:46,946
our last longboat
was safe and secure.

1085
01:20:50,508 --> 01:20:51,736
Well...

1086
01:20:53,108 --> 01:20:54,905
that should hold it.

1087
01:20:54,948 --> 01:20:57,542
I taught you too well.

1088
01:20:59,508 --> 01:21:02,944
If you don't mind,
we'd just as soon avoid prison.

1089
01:21:02,988 --> 01:21:06,424
Little Morphy here,
he's a free spirit.

1090
01:21:07,948 --> 01:21:12,703
Being in a cage,
it'd break his heart.

1091
01:21:28,268 --> 01:21:31,624
What say you ship out
with us, lad?

1092
01:21:31,668 --> 01:21:33,863
You and me,
Hawkins and Silver...

1093
01:21:33,908 --> 01:21:38,504
full of ourselves
and no ties to anyone!

1094
01:21:40,628 --> 01:21:44,746
You know,
when I got on this boat...

1095
01:21:44,788 --> 01:21:48,701
I would've taken you up
on that offer in a second...

1096
01:21:48,748 --> 01:21:52,980
but I met this old cyborg...

1097
01:21:53,028 --> 01:21:56,225
and he taught me that
I could chart my own course.

1098
01:21:58,868 --> 01:22:00,381
That's what I'm gonna do.

1099
01:22:00,428 --> 01:22:06,697
And what do you see
of that pal of yours?

1100
01:22:06,748 --> 01:22:08,261
A future.

1101
01:22:08,308 --> 01:22:10,742
Why...

1102
01:22:10,788 --> 01:22:15,623
Iook at ya,
glowing like a solar fire.

1103
01:22:15,668 --> 01:22:18,228
You're something special, Jim.

1104
01:22:18,268 --> 01:22:22,261
You're gonna rattle the stars,
you are.

1105
01:22:30,708 --> 01:22:34,747
Got a bit of grease
in this cyborg eye of mine.

1106
01:22:38,788 --> 01:22:42,383
Hey, Morph.
I'll see ya around, OK?

1107
01:22:42,428 --> 01:22:43,656
See ya around.

1108
01:22:52,548 --> 01:22:56,097
Morphy, I got a job for ya.

1109
01:22:56,148 --> 01:23:01,176
I need you to keep an eye
on this here pup.

1110
01:23:03,428 --> 01:23:05,942
Will ya do me
that little favour?

1111
01:23:05,988 --> 01:23:07,501
Aye-aye, Captain.

1112
01:23:14,148 --> 01:23:17,504
And one more thing.

1113
01:23:17,548 --> 01:23:19,857
This is for your dear mother...

1114
01:23:19,908 --> 01:23:22,900
to rebuild that inn of hers.

1115
01:23:24,948 --> 01:23:25,068
Stay out of trouble,
ya old scallywag.

1116
01:23:25,068 --> 01:23:27,980
Stay out of trouble,
ya old scallywag.

1117
01:23:28,028 --> 01:23:33,341
Why, Jimbo, lad,
when have I ever done otherwise?

1118
01:25:34,428 --> 01:25:38,706
It's good to see the sun
and feel this place

1119
01:25:38,748 --> 01:25:42,582
This place I never thought
would feel like home

1120
01:25:42,628 --> 01:25:45,062
And I ran forever

1121
01:25:45,108 --> 01:25:46,826
Far away

1122
01:25:46,868 --> 01:25:51,259
And I always thought
I'd end up here alone

1123
01:25:51,308 --> 01:25:54,778
Somehow the world has changed

1124
01:25:54,828 --> 01:25:57,501
And I've come home

1125
01:25:57,548 --> 01:26:01,063
To give you back the things
they took from you

1126
01:26:01,108 --> 01:26:03,417
And I feel you now

1127
01:26:03,468 --> 01:26:05,743
I'm not alone

1128
01:26:05,788 --> 01:26:11,545
I always know where you are

1129
01:26:11,588 --> 01:26:13,943
When I see myself

1130
01:26:13,988 --> 01:26:20,063
I always know where you are

1131
01:26:20,108 --> 01:26:24,863
Where you are

1132
01:26:24,908 --> 01:26:28,696
And I found something
that was always there

1133
01:26:28,748 --> 01:26:32,900
Sometimes it's got to hurt
before you feel

1134
01:26:32,948 --> 01:26:37,180
But now I'm strong,
and I won't kneel

1135
01:26:37,228 --> 01:26:41,346
Except to thank
who's watching over me

1136
01:26:41,388 --> 01:26:45,097
And somehow I feel so strong

1137
01:26:45,148 --> 01:26:47,537
And I've begun

1138
01:26:47,588 --> 01:26:51,137
To be the one
I never thought I'd be

1139
01:26:51,188 --> 01:26:53,065
And I feel you now

1140
01:26:53,108 --> 01:26:55,542
I'm not alone

1141
01:26:55,588 --> 01:27:01,424
I always know where you are

1142
01:27:01,468 --> 01:27:03,823
And when I see myself

1143
01:27:03,868 --> 01:27:09,977
I always know where you are

1144
01:27:10,028 --> 01:27:15,148
Where you are

1145
01:27:15,188 --> 01:27:18,578
Now it's all so clear

1146
01:27:18,628 --> 01:27:20,903
And I believe

1147
01:27:20,948 --> 01:27:24,657
That everything's been
opened up to me

1148
01:27:24,708 --> 01:27:26,699
And I feel you now

1149
01:27:26,748 --> 01:27:30,741
I'm not alone, I always know

1150
01:27:30,788 --> 01:27:37,182
I always know where you are

1151
01:27:37,228 --> 01:27:39,298
And when I see myself

1152
01:27:39,348 --> 01:27:45,503
I always know where you are

1153
01:27:45,548 --> 01:27:47,459
And when I feel the sun

1154
01:27:47,508 --> 01:27:53,663
I always know where you are

1155
